  29 Nov 2004; Chris White <chriswhite@gentoo.org> openexr-1.0.7.ebuild:
  Marked 1.0.7 stable. Test case was running with FEATURES=maketest and using
  sample images from the homepage and a test program.

  28 Nov 2004; Chris White <chriswhite@gentoo.org> metadata.xml:
  Taking over as maintainer.

*openexr-1.2.1 (10 Sep 2004)

  10 Sep 2004; <blubb@gentoo.org> +openexr-1.2.1.ebuild:
  version bump. Thanks to Carsten Lohrke for providing this ebuild.

  27 Apr 2004; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> openexr-1.0.6.ebuild,
  openexr-1.0.7.ebuild:
  Add inherit eutils

  02 Mar 2004; David Holm <dholm@gentoo.org> openexr-1.0.7.ebuild:
  Added to ~ppc.

*openexr-1.0.7 (02 Mar 2004)

  02 Mar 2004; Martin Holzer <mholzer@gentoo.org> openexr-1.0.7.ebuild:
  Version bumped. Closes 37646

*openexr-1.0.6 (16 Oct 2003)

  16 Oct 2003; Brandy Westcott brandy@gentoo.org metadata.xml,
  openexr-1.0.6.ebuild:
  Initial import. OpenEXR is an image format developed by Industrial Light
  & Magic. A big thanks to Henti Smith <henti@geekware.co.za> for providing
  the ebuild (see Bug #14415)
  
  Added initial ChangeLog which should be updated whenever the package is
  updated in any way. This changelog is targetted to users. This means that the
  comments should well explained and written in clean English. The details about
  writing correct changelogs are explained in the skel.ChangeLog file which you
  can find in the root directory of the portage repository.

